center for medieval and early modern studies skip to main content home login center for medieval and early modern studies enter your keywords main menu about programs courses people blogs news calendar resources you are here home the poetry and art of italy's jewish tombstones presenter david malkiel co sponsored by the department of religious studies and the taube center for jewish studies david malkiel associate professor of jewish history at bar ilan university is a scholar of jewish political structure society and culture during and after the renaissance his current project is a study of what can be learned from tombstones of italian jews in the period between 1529 1562 tombstones that feature poetry in a broad range of metrical and rhyme schemes and address subjects like faith love loss and hope professor malkiel is currently writing stones speak a study of the paduan material's inscriptions art and society and another study is soon to appear poems in marble inscriptions from the jewish cemeteries of padua 1529 1862 date november 29 2011 12 00pm 1 30pm location bldg 360 conference room center for medieval and early modern studies pigott hall building 260 450 serra mall stanford ca 94350 director cecile alduy alduy stanford edu web manager biliana kassabova bilianak stanford edu facebook contact map & directions
